&gt; Then she was serious. &quot;I hope you haven&#39;t turned Autobot on us?&quot; If 
&gt; empath was still a Decepticon & a good Seeker as she was or 
currently 
&gt; is on Cybertron, then she could be trusted with what Maxima had in 
&gt; mind.

&quot;Autobot?  Never!&quot; Empath laughs, flaring her wings and showing off 
the familiar purple insignia of the Decepticons.  &quot;But I am aligned 
with these Maximals for the time being, on a matter of revenge.&quot;

&lt;I&#39;ll explain later,&gt; she tells Maxima telepathically.

Her clear optics watched her for a moment. Then she nodded. She better 
explain herself.


&gt; Windlord arrived where the femmes were &quot;An old workmate, I guess?&quot; thought 
&gt; the male hoping that Emphat could read his mind.
&gt; 
&gt; 

She turned to look at Windlord. &quot;You could say that.&quot;

&gt; &lt;Of course I can read your mind, love,&gt; she tells him.  Aloud, she 
&gt; says, &quot;Windlord, this is Maxima.  We used to bash Autobots together.&quot;
&gt; 

Looking up at Windlord. She felt a little ashamed in this form. She seemed 
nothing of the impressive Decepticon she once was. How she remembered it. She 
would regain her old form... & soon.

&gt; 
&gt; Ragnar looked at her with a black glance and muttered in his head.
&gt; 
&gt; Ragnar: I&#39;ll drag her in a trial of grievance and kill her... I am
&gt; Ghost Bear, for Kerensky&#39;s sake!
&gt; 
&gt; Meanwhile, Blackfang tried to handle the arrival of the tiger lady.
&gt; 
&gt; Blackfang: Well, (he looked around at Empath and Windlord) it looks
&gt; like I am only part of the commitee. Name&#39;s Blackfang. We&#39;ll give you
&gt; a room and access to a part of our installations, but you will have to
&gt; be under constant surveillance. I hope you&#39;ll forgive us, but we don&#39;t
&gt; take Decepticons lightly.
&gt; 
Glancing back at this Blackfang, growling. She ignored the fool then stepped 
closer to Empath. &quot;I have a favor to ask of you.&quot; she glanced about. &quot;We 
should discuss this in private.&quot;  

She looked at the others, &quot;If you will excuse us... Gentlemen.&quot; she stressed, 
growling. Decepticons stuck together. Padding off away from the others, still 
outside. Would be better outside that way no one would listen, since they had 
that inside for sure.


